;; EM-1 (edge-matrix, 2026-07-02): a quoted form (reader sugar ', `, or a
;; #(...) literal) as the BODY of any let-family form silently truncates
;; the rest of the program at parse level. Same class as bug #229 (and/or
;; arg dispatch dropped quote/vector tokens), now in the let-body parser.
;;
;; Found by: pair008_quote__tail_position (quote_sym__in__tail_position_
;; let_tail_in_define), reproduces under BOTH -r and AOT, exit 0 (!).
;;
;; Expected output:  before / es / after
;; Actual output:    before        (everything from the let form on is DROPPED)
;;
;; Inside a define the same shape instead errors with
;; "expected closing parenthesis after variable value" /
;; "Undefined variable: es".
(display "before") (newline)
(display (let ((u 1)) 'es)) (newline)
(display "after") (newline)
